RACE.RACE_TEXT: GREAT MEADOW RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 40000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAMPOLDI PLAN led from the start, drew off after the final hurdle. ROCKET ONE raced close up in fourth, closed willingly from the final turn to the wire, not troubling winner. CIBOLIAN was unhurried from the start, rallied on the final turn and closed for third. IMPERIAL ASSASSIN (IRE) was never far back, and finished evenly. REWIND (GB) raced held up and had no finishing rally. GIRL DAD was never a factor and tired. AGITARE (IRE) showed early speed, traveled on a wide trip jumping to the right, then tired. GUN FOR SUCCESS trailed. ABSAM traveled up with the pace till the final turn, then tired and gave way. FLOP SHOT (IRE) unseated the rider at the first hurdle.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Steeplethon S. GREAT MEADOW RACE 2 3M Timber CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 30000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. 160 lbs. Winners of a steeplethon, 5 lbs. extra.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORM TEAM settled in a stalking position in third, ridden to lead before the final turn, pushed out clear on the turn and remained in command to the wire. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Speedy Smithwick Memorial S. GREAT MEADOW RACE 6 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 50000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEARS OLD. 148 lbs. Winners, other than claiming, 3 lbs. extra for each race won.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOFFMAN (IRE) opened up a huge margin, jumped fluently throughout, finished far ahead of rivals, but was disqualified when reported missing a beacon, confirmed by video replay, thus off course.
